paragraph.text:
Authorize, approve, renew, modify, or extend any experimental, pilot, or demonstration project under 
              section 1115 of the Social Security Act (
                42 U.S.C. 1315
              ) that waives compliance with a requirement of 
              section 407 of such Act (
                42 U.S.C. 607
              ) through a waiver of 
              section 402 of such Act (
                42 U.S.C. 602
              ) or that provides authority for an expenditure which would not otherwise be an allowable use of funds under a State program funded under 
              part A of title IV of such Act (
                42 U.S.C. 601 et seq.
              ) with respect to compliance with the work requirements in section 407 of such Act to be regarded as an allowable use of funds under that program for any period.
